HEADWORD: Harpings
<hw>Harp"ings</hw> <pr>(-⟦icr⟧ngz)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>The fore parts of the wales, which encompass the
bow of a vessel, and are fastened to the stem.</def> <altsp>[Written
also <asp>harpins</asp>.]</altsp> <rj><au>Totten.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

